		<h2> The Bundle class </h2>
		A bundle is generally used for passing data between various Activities of android. <br>
		The following code will start up an activity and pass to it some values.
<pre class="code">
Intent intent = new
Intent( getApplicationContext(), SecondActivity.class );
intent.putExtra( "myKey", someValues );  
startActivity( intent );
</pre>
		Then, in the sencod activity, you can sue the bundle just like an HashMap.
<pre class="code">
Bundle extras = intent.getExtras(); 
Object someValues = extras.get( "myKey" );
</pre>
